==English==
===Noun===
'''glyph''' ([[glyphs]])
# A three dimensional object representing a real item, such as an airplane, often created thru magic or some form of conjuring.

# A single formed character or symbol, usually representing a letter in a [[font]]. A glyph can be anything from the number 5, to the letter 'F', to a piece of textual decoration.

